The National Union of Mineworkers demands justice after the death of four miners in a rockfall at the Tau Lekoa mine near Orkney. JOHANNESBURG - NUM is calling for an independent investigation after four mineworkers died at the Tau Lekoa mine in Orkney in the North West. A fifth miner was rescued with serious injuries on Friday after the accident. READ: Fourth miner's body found "The last person we talked to said: 'We are suffocating please, bring us some oxygen'," said NUM president Joseph Montisetse. NUM said action must be taken if mine safety regulations were breached. READ: Three miners' bodies recovered from Tau Lekoa mine The miners were trapped underground after a tremor caused a rockfall. Last year, 81 people died in the country's mines, according to the department of mineral resources. - Additional reporting AFP